reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic water bottle
reviews.reviewText: We love these bottles. We bought them because we go on cruises where we're not allowed to bring plastic bottles on board.Now that we've had them for so long, we find we use them at home more and more. My regular bottle brush fits inside perfectly. They fit well in my car cup holder, and they keep our cold drinks cold for hours.The only negative is that the height sometimes is incompatible with water refill stations in airports. That's not the fault of the bottle. These are a bargain.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Keeps the temperature of the drink; opening is not ideal size
reviews.reviewText: This is fairly nice insulated stainless steel water bottle that I ordered for my husband. It really keeps the temperature of the drink constant. Cold drinks stay cold for quite a long time. He hasn't used it with hot drinks. He did once place room temperature water in the bottle and then took it into the cold for several hours. The water remained room temperature, which wasn't the case, but showed us how well it was insulated.One of the downsides to the bottle is that the opening is rather small. I can fit a bottle brush in it when cleaning it, but even that is a bit of a challenge. And if you are someone who wants ice in your drink, you'll need to get some very small cubes or crushed ice.This is a good value for the money though. So if you're on a budget and looking for a quality insulated water bottle, you'll likely be pleased (as long the small opening doesn't bother you).
